<br>
Now having said that, I will adnmit that I frequently &quot;port for donations.&quot; I am like every other druid out there. I need money. I hate farming and I suck at kiting so ports are an easy to to do it. Now when i port, I never set a price. WHen asked what I charge I say donations. Whatever you feel like paying (I have that hot keyed). What happens when some smart @$$ darkelf donates nothing or worse 3cp? Nothing. I wish them well and good journies.<br>
<br>
Also let it be said that I do set prices for ports at times. If someone (who I don't know) gives me a tell for a port, my response is always. Sure for 500pp up front. Reason I picked 500pp? Because that's an outragious amount and hopefully the person realizes I'm being sarcastic and that I have no interest in porting them. Plus if anyon takes me up then I just made off very well.<br>
<br>
Ok not really sure this is a rant, but I'm a nice wood elf druid. It the best I can do.<br>
<br>
Please feel free to respond. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rtfm>rtfm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/6/01 2:30:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> set price for donations</span><hr size=1> People set prices for donations all the time.<br>
<br>
From charity/fundraising carwashes to raffle tickets.<br>
<br>
To the boy scouts picking up your old christmas tree for 10 bucks.<br>
<br>
Frankly, though I would rather see, &quot;Porting to all locations, 10pp a seat&quot;, that way some real noob would not waste their time tossing a tell when he only has 6gps.<br>
<br>
And that said, I have had much better experiences picking off the &quot;Can someone port me to DL for 30pp&quot;, than advertising myself.<br>
<br>
I remember one time, at the Orc Fort, my enchanter group mate saw one for 100pp to DL, she says &quot;arn't you going to take that, that's a lot of money&quot;.  Beamed her a smile, and just kept on killing them orcs.<br>
<br>
I have no set price myself either, from free to a quest gem.  Just depends on my mood. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uanadcloudrider.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anad Cloudrider</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/25/01 6:27:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sowing/Porting/Buffing for donations</span><hr size=1> I can't port yet...need 4 more lvls, but I know that that is the real money maker for us druids...nothing else will get you pp quicker. <br>
<br>
As for sow, buff, and binding for donations...I do it for exactly what I shout out for...donations. A majority of the time people will give anywhere from 2pp to 10pp as a donation but I haven't turned anyone down for whatever they offered. One of the nice things about having sow is that when I see a shout by an enchanter &quot;casting breeze/clarity/clarity II for donations&quot; I have yet to come across one that turned me down when I offered sow for their services. I love them chanters ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uallyssiainny.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Allyssia Inny</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ichuu.com/KittyIcon.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/26/01 8:09:24 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.ichuu.com/cotrd/AllyPhoto.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sowing/Porting/Buffing for donations</span><hr size=1> I think accepting donations for lower level buffs and ports is fine.  I haven't charged since I turned 45.  I won't charge for ports or buffs, strangers or not.  I don't need the pp that much and I don't feel right taking from someone else.  Heh, shrug personal opinion. :)<br>
<br>
Ally. <p><BR>
<a href="http://www.ichuu.com/cotrd/allyprofile.html" target="AllyProfile"><img src="http://www.ichuu.com/ally60.gif" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upatofnaud.showPublicProfile?language=EN>patofnaud</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/27/01 6:51:27 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sowing/Porting/Buffing for donations</span><hr size=1> This is an age old debate..<br>
<br>
One thing that is constantly neglected is this,,,<br>
<br>
Mana is free, Time is not.<br>
<br>
When you level 45, you can dump SoW, Skin, Regen, Lev, Str and BARELY use a bub of manna. The you can regen standing up in about 5 or 10 minutes, give or take. NET = No big deal.<br>
<br>
BUT, when you are level 24, those buffs (sans regen), well that pretty much eats most of your mana bar. NET = 20 mins downtime ;(<br>
<br>
Folk don't realize, even at 35, if I am in WC, do a mercy port to NK for corpse run port, then pop back to WC, I am basically at 40m. Then someone ask me to take them to DL, sigh, ok. Now I am in DL and 10m. Now I am sitting on my butt for about 20 min. NET = about 35 minutes of lost exp, 35 minutes of lost TIME.<br>
<br>
SoW's, they dont make a dent in my manna bar, so I do them all day long... Never charge, but never hit cancle if money drops in a trade window. ;)<br>
<br>
Oh, and power leveling? If I have time, SURE! For 100pp per 30 minutes paid in advance. ;) <p><body lang=EN-US style='tab-interval:.5in'>

