Both."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usyldane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>syldane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/23/01 5:53:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sowing/Porting/Buffing for donations</span><hr size=1> At the higher levels these days, I usually don't get bothered with port requests from strangers, and a few pp usually isn't enough to pull me away from whatever it is that I'm doing.  I think you will find that standing around auctioning teleport services isn't something you'll be doing when you get into the 50's.  Most people playing in your level range have friends that can teleport them around.  On that note, your guild, raidgroup, and friends will keep you teleporting all the time anyway, and you won't have the desire to advertise for more.  Your time will be much better spent in some dungeon somewhere, raiding for good loot and exp. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usyldane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>syldane</A> at: 10/23/01 5:53:27 am<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessage?topicID=574.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessage?topicID=530.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.emailToFriend?topicID=546.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.threadControl?topicID=546.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 a